text: Hi all, I'm just about to start learning to develop for Android, I'd really appreciate if you could mention some good/recommended resources to start. :simple_smile:

attachments.text: Everything you need to start developing apps for Android is available here on <http://developer.android.com|developer.android.com> . You'll find everything from the API documentation and design guidelines, to information about the current device landscape and how you can distribute…

text: <@U060Q25GC>  No problem. Also if you don't know java I would learn that first.
I remember looking at the same Android projects too, when I was first learning Android
IIRC Android Studio lets you import those pretty easily..

<@U060Q25GC>: 
at the start go through official tutorials and guides
<https://developer.android.com/guide/index.html> 
<https://developer.android.com/training/index.html>

if you are looking for a book, I can also recommend next books
Android Recipes: A Problem-Solution Approach by Dave Smith
Busy developer's guide to Android by commonsware

a good book was Professional Android by Reto Meier, but now it's outdated

Later, when you are comfortable with Android concepts and SDK, start looking at open sourced apps. E.g. Github for Android or Google IO app.
